<DOC><DOCNO> AP890129-0026 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-01-29-89 1422EST</FILEID><FIRST>r w AM-Bush     01-29 0167</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Bush,150</SECOND><HEAD>President Nursing Cold</HEAD><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   President Bush cancelled a planned visit to thepresidential retreat at Camp David on Sunday and stayed home at theWhite House to nurse a persistent cold.   Bush, whose first full week in office was marked by long workinghours and frequent short trips about town, decided to take it easyin hopes of conquering the cold that by week's end had left hisvoice noticeably raspy, according to aides.   ``He just has a cold, a regular cold,and is taking somedecongestants,'' said spokesman Bruce Zanca.   Bush had planned to travel by helicopter to Camp David in thenearby mountains of Maryland and spend most of the day there. He hadinvited House Speaker Jim Wright, D-Texas, and his wife to join himthere for what White House aides said was to have been a purelysocial gettogether.   Bush's hoarseness was evident Friday at his first news conferenceas president. ``I sound worse than I feel,'' he said.</TEXT></DOC>